## Build

```bash
export ESPFOC_PATH=/path/to/espFoC
idf.py set-target {target}
idf.py build flash monitor
```

The app boots straight into the parked regulation callback. Edit
`main/main.c::parked_regulation_cb` to wire your application logic
(speed loop, position loop, command source, ...).

## Re-tune at any time

The runtime tuner stays compiled in. Connect TunerStudio to retune
without rebuilding firmware:

```bash
PYTHONPATH=tools python3 -m espfoc_studio.gui --port /dev/ttyACM0
```

When happy, click **Save to NVS** in the GUI and the new gains
survive a reboot.
